This article is a transcript of President Trump's remarks during a St. Patrick's Day celebration at the U.S. Capitol. He thanks the attendees, including Vice President Pence and members of Congress, for joining him. The President welcomes Taoiseach and mentions their previous acquaintance. He also acknowledges Ambassador Mulhall and his wife, as well as the Irish delegation. President Trump highlights the strong bonds between the United States and Ireland, with over 30 million Americans claiming Irish heritage. He mentions notable Americans of Irish descent and their achievements, including President Kennedy and astronaut Michael Collins. The President celebrates the toughness and resilience of the Irish people and expresses his excitement for the future. He concludes by thanking everyone and joking about trade taxes.